===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|nightingale}}, {{m|enm|niȝtingale}}, alteration (with intrusive ''n'') of {{m|enm|nightegale}}, from {{inh|en|ang|nihtegala}}, {{m|ang|nihtegale||nightingale; night-raven|lit=night-singer}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*nahtigalǭ||nightingale}}, equivalent to {{compound|en|night|gale}}. Cognate with Saterland Frisian {{m|stq|Noachtegoal||nightingale}}, Dutch {{m|nl|nachtegaal||nightingale}}, German Low German {{m|nds-de|Nachtigall||nightingale}}, German {{m|de|Nachtigall||nightingale}}, Danish {{m|da|nattergal||nightingale}}, Swedish {{m|sv|näktergal||nightingale}}, Icelandic {{m|is|næturgali||nightingale}}.

